429	9	A.6.2.2	Teleworking	Teleworking	Telewerken	A policy and supporting security measures should be implemented to protect information accessed, processed or stored at teleworking sites.	A policy and supporting security measures should be implemented to protect information accessed, processed or stored at teleworking sites.	Beleid en ondersteunende beveiligingsmaatregelen behoren te worden gemplementeerd ter beveiliging van informatie die vanaf telewerklocaties wordt benaderd, verwerkt of opgeslagen.	226
430	10	A.7.1.1	Screening	Screening	Screening	Background verification checks on all candidates for employment should be carried out in accordance with relevant laws, regulations and ethics and should be proportional to the business requirements, the classification of the information to be accessed and the perceived risks.	Background verification checks on all candidates for employment should be carried out in accordance with relevant laws, regulations and ethics and should be proportional to the business requirements, the classification of the information to be accessed and the perceived risks.	Verificatie van de achtergrond van alle kandidaten voor een dienstverband behoort te worden uitgevoerd in overeenstemming met relevante wet- en regelgeving en ethische overwegingen en behoort in verhouding te staan tot de bedrijfseisen, de classificatie van de informatie waartoe toegang wordt verleend en de vastgestelde risicos te zijn.	227
431	11	A.7.1.2	Terms and conditions of employment	Terms and conditions of employment	Arbeidsvoorwaarden	The contractual agreements with employees and contractors should state their and the organizations responsibilities for information security.	The contractual agreements with employees and contractors should state their and the organizations responsibilities for information security.	De contractuele overeenkomst met medewerkers en contractanten behoort hun verantwoordelijkheden voor informatiebeveiliging en die van de organisatie te vermelden.	227
432	12	A.7.2.1	Management responsibilities	Management responsibilities	Directieverantwoordelijkheden	Management should require all employees and contractors to apply information security in accordance with the established policies and procedures of the organization.	Management should require all employees and contractors to apply information security in accordance with the established policies and procedures of the organization.	De directie behoort van alle medewerkers en contractanten te eisen dat ze informatiebeveiliging toepassen in overeenstemming met de vastgestelde beleidsregels en procedures van de organisatie.	228
443	23	A.8.3.1	Management of removable media	Management of removable media	Beheer van verwijderbare media	Procedures should be implemented for the management of removable media in accordance with the classification scheme adopted by the organization.	Procedures should be implemented for the management of removable media in accordance with the classification scheme adopted by the organization.	Voor het beheren van verwijderbare media behoren procedures te worden gemplementeerd in overeenstemming met het classificatieschema dat door de organisatie is vastgesteld.	232
433	13	A.7.2.2	Information security awareness, education and training	Information security awareness, education and training	Bewustzijn, opleiding en training ten aanzien van informatiebeveiliging	All employees of the organization and, where relevant, contractors should receive appropriate awareness education and training and regular updates in organizational policies and procedures, as relevant for their job function.	All employees of the organization and, where relevant, contractors should receive appropriate awareness education and training and regular updates in organizational policies and procedures, as relevant for their job function.	Alle medewerkers van de organisatie en, voor zover relevant, contractanten behoren een passende bewustzijnsopleiding en -training te krijgen en regelmatige bijscholing van beleidsregels en procedures van de organisatie, voor zover relevant voor hun functie.	228
434	14	A.7.2.3	Disciplinary process	Disciplinary process	Disciplinaire procedure	There should be a formal and communicated disciplinary process in place to take action against employees who have committed an information security breach.	There should be a formal and communicated disciplinary process in place to take action against employees who have committed an information security breach.	Er behoort een formele en gecommuniceerde disciplinaire procedure te zijn om actie te ondernemen tegen medewerkers die een inbreuk hebben gepleegd op de informatiebeveiliging.	228
435	15	A.7.3.1	Termination or change of employment responsibilities	Termination or change of employment responsibilities	Beindiging of wijziging van verantwoordelijkheden van het dienstverband	Information security responsibilities and duties that remain valid after termination or change of employment should be defined, communicated to the employee or contractor and enforced.	Information security responsibilities and duties that remain valid after termination or change of employment should be defined, communicated to the employee or contractor and enforced.	Verantwoordelijkheden en taken met betrekking tot informatiebeveiliging die van kracht blijven na beindiging of wijziging van het dienstverband behoren te worden gedefinieerd, gecommuniceerd aan de medewerker of contractant, en ten uitvoer gebracht.	229
436	16	A.8.1.1	Inventory of assets	Inventory of assets	Inventariseren van bedrijfsmiddelen	Information, other assets associated with information and information processing facilities should be identified and an inventory of these assets should be drawn up and maintained.	Information, other assets associated with information and information processing facilities should be identified and an inventory of these assets should be drawn up and maintained.	Bedrijfsmiddelen die samenhangen met informatie en informatieverwerkende faciliteiten behoren te worden gedentificeerd, en van deze bedrijfsmiddelen behoort een inventaris te worden opgesteld en onderhouden.	230
437	17	A.8.1.2	Ownership of assets	Ownership of assets	Eigendom van bedrijfsmiddelen	Assets maintained in the inventory should be owned.	Assets maintained in the inventory should be owned.	Bedrijfsmiddelen die in het inventarisoverzicht worden bijgehouden, behoren een eigenaar te hebben.	230
438	18	A.8.1.3	Acceptable use of assets	Acceptable use of assets	Aanvaardbaar gebruik van bedrijfsmiddelen	Rules for the acceptable use of information and of assets associated with information and information processing facilities should be identified, documented and implemented.	Rules for the acceptable use of information and of assets associated with information and information processing facilities should be identified, documented and implemented.	Voor het aanvaardbaar gebruik van informatie en van bedrijfsmiddelen die samenhangen met informatie en informatieverwerkende faciliteiten behoren regels te worden gedentificeerd, gedocumenteerd en gemplementeerd.	230
439	19	A.8.1.4	Return of assets	Return of assets	Teruggeven van bedrijfsmiddelen	All employees and external party users should return all of the organizational assets in their possession upon termination of their employment, contract or agreement.	All employees and external party users should return all of the organizational assets in their possession upon termination of their employment, contract or agreement.	Alle medewerkers en externe gebruikers behoren alle bedrijfsmiddelen van de organisatie die ze in hun bezit hebben bij beindiging van hun dienstverband, contract of overeenkomst terug te geven.	230
440	20	A.8.2.1	Classification of information	Classification of information	Classificatie van informatie	Information should be classified in terms of legal requirements, value, criticality and sensitivity to unauthorised disclosure or modification.	Information should be classified in terms of legal requirements, value, criticality and sensitivity to unauthorised disclosure or modification.	Informatie behoort te worden geclassificeerd met betrekking tot wettelijke eisen, waarde, belang en gevoeligheid voor onbevoegde bekendmaking of wijziging.	231
441	21	A.8.2.2	Labelling of information	Labelling of information	Informatie labelen	An appropriate set of procedures for information labelling should be developed and implemented in accordance with the information classification scheme adopted by the organization. "Implementation guidance" Procedures for information labelling need to cover information and its related assets in physical and electronic formats. The labelling should reflect the classification scheme established in 8.2.1 . The labels should be easily recognizable. The procedures should give guidance on where and how labels are attached in consideration of how the information is accessed or the assets are handled depending on the types of media. The procedures can define cases where labelling is omitted, e. g. labelling of non-confidential information to reduce workloads. Employees and contractors should be made aware of labelling procedures. Output from systems containing information that is classified as being sensitive or critical should carry an appropriate classification label.	An appropriate set of procedures for information labelling should be developed and implemented in accordance with the information classification scheme adopted by the organization. "Implementation guidance" Procedures for information labelling need to cover information and its related assets in physical and electronic formats. The labelling should reflect the classification scheme established in 8.2.1 . The labels should be easily recognizable. The procedures should give guidance on where and how labels are attached in consideration of how the information is accessed or the assets are handled depending on the types of media. The procedures can define cases where labelling is omitted, e. g. labelling of non-confidential information to reduce workloads. Employees and contractors should be made aware of labelling procedures. Output from systems containing information that is classified as being sensitive or critical should carry an appropriate classification label.	Om informatie te labelen behoort een passende reeks procedures te worden ontwikkeld en gemplementeerd in overeenstemming met het informatieclassificatieschema dat is vastgesteld door de organisatie.	231
442	22	A.8.2.3	Handling of assets	Handling of assets	Behandelen van bedrijfsmiddelen	Procedures for handling assets should be developed and implemented in accordance with the information classification scheme adopted by the organization.	Procedures for handling assets should be developed and implemented in accordance with the information classification scheme adopted by the organization.	Procedures voor het behandelen van bedrijfsmiddelen behoren te worden ontwikkeld en gemplementeerd in overeenstemming met het informatieclassificatieschema dat is vastgesteld door de organisatie.	231
445	25	A.8.3.3	Physical media transfer	Physical media transfer	Media fysiek overdragen	Media containing information should be protected against unauthorized access, misuse or corruption during transportation.	Media containing information should be protected against unauthorized access, misuse or corruption during transportation.	Media die informatie bevatten, behoren te worden beschermd tegen onbevoegde toegang, misbruik of corruptie tijdens transport.	232
446	26	A.9.1.1	Access control policy	Access control policy	Beleid voor toegangsbeveiliging	An access control policy should be established, documented and reviewed based on business and information security requirements.	An access control policy should be established, documented and reviewed based on business and information security requirements.	Een beleid voor toegangsbeveiliging behoort te worden vastgesteld, gedocumenteerd en beoordeeld op basis van bedrijfs- en informatiebeveiligingseisen.	233
447	27	A.9.1.2	Access to networks and network services	Access to networks and network services	Toegang tot netwerken en netwerkdiensten	Users should only be provided with access to the network and network services that they have been specifically authorized to use.	Users should only be provided with access to the network and network services that they have been specifically authorized to use.	Gebruikers behoren alleen toegang te krijgen tot het netwerk en de netwerkdiensten waarvoor zij specifiek bevoegd zijn.	233
448	28	A.9.2.1	User registration and de-registration	User registration and de-registration	Registratie en uitschrijving van gebruikers	A formal user registration and de-registration process should be implemented to enable assignment of access rights.	A formal user registration and de-registration process should be implemented to enable assignment of access rights.	Een formele registratie- en afmeldingsprocedure behoort te worden gemplementeerd om toewijzing van toegangsrechten mogelijk te maken.	234
449	29	A.9.2.2	User access provisioning	User access provisioning	Gebruikers toegang verlenen	A formal user access provisioning process should be implemented to assign or revoke access rights for all user types to all systems and services.	A formal user access provisioning process should be implemented to assign or revoke access rights for all user types to all systems and services.	Een formele gebruikerstoegangsverleningsprocedure behoort te worden gemplementeerd om toegangsrechten voor alle typen gebruikers en voor alle systemen en diensten toe te wijzen of in te trekken.	234
450	30	A.9.2.3	Management of privileged access rights	Management of privileged access rights	Beheren van speciale toegangsrechten	The allocation and use of privileged access rights should be restricted and controlled.	The allocation and use of privileged access rights should be restricted and controlled.	Het toewijzen en gebruik van speciale toegangsrechten behoren te worden beperkt en beheerst.	234
451	31	A.9.2.4	Management of secret authentication information of users	Management of secret authentication information of users	Beheer van geheime authenticatie-informatie van gebruikers	The allocation of secret authentication information should be controlled through a formal management process.	The allocation of secret authentication information should be controlled through a formal management process.	Het toewijzen van geheime authenticatie-informatie behoort te worden beheerst via een formeel beheersproces.	234
452	32	A.9.2.5	Review of user access rights	Review of user access rights	Beoordeling van toegangsrechten van gebruikers	Asset owners should review users access rights at regular intervals.	Asset owners should review users access rights at regular intervals.	Eigenaren van bedrijfsmiddelen behoren toegangsrechten van gebruikers regelmatig te beoordelen.	234
453	33	A.9.2.6	Removal or adjustment of access rights	Removal or adjustment of access rights	Toegangsrechten intrekken of aanpassen	The access rights of all employees and external party users to information and information processing facilities should be removed upon termination of their employment, contract or agreement, or adjusted upon change.	The access rights of all employees and external party users to information and information processing facilities should be removed upon termination of their employment, contract or agreement, or adjusted upon change.	De toegangsrechten van alle medewerkers en externe gebruikers voor informatie en informatieverwerkende faciliteiten behoren bij beindiging van hun dienstverband, contract of overeenkomst te worden verwijderd, en bij wijzigingen behoren ze te worden aangepast.	234
454	34	A.9.3.1	Use of secret authentication information	Use of secret authentication information	Geheime authenticatie-informatie gebruiken	Users should be required to follow the organizations practices in the use of secret authentication information.	Users should be required to follow the organizations practices in the use of secret authentication information.	Van gebruikers behoort te worden verlangd dat zij zich bij het gebruiken van geheime authenticatie-informatie houden aan de praktijk van de organisatie.	235
455	35	A.9.4.1	Information access restriction	Information access restriction	Beperking toegang tot informatie	Access to information and application system functions should be restricted in accordance with the access control policy.	Access to information and application system functions should be restricted in accordance with the access control policy.	Toegang tot informatie en systeemfuncties van toepassingen behoort te worden beperkt in overeenstemming met het beleid voor toegangsbeveiliging.	236
456	36	A.9.4.2	Secure log-on procedures	Secure log-on procedures	Beveiligde inlogprocedures	Where required by the access control policy, access to systems and applications should be controlled by a secure log-on procedure.	Where required by the access control policy, access to systems and applications should be controlled by a secure log-on procedure.	Indien het beleid voor toegangsbeveiliging dit vereist, behoort toegang tot systemen en toepassingen te worden beheerst door een beveiligde inlogprocedure.	236
457	37	A.9.4.3	Password management system	Password management system	Systeem voor wachtwoordbeheer	Password management systems should be interactive and should ensure quality passwords.	Password management systems should be interactive and should ensure quality passwords.	Systemen voor wachtwoordbeheer behoren interactief te zijn en sterke wachtwoorden te waarborgen.	236
458	38	A.9.4.4	Use of privileged utility programs	Use of privileged utility programs	Speciale systeemhulpmiddelen gebruiken	The use of utility programs that might be capable of overriding system and application controls should be restricted and tightly controlled.	The use of utility programs that might be capable of overriding system and application controls should be restricted and tightly controlled.	Het gebruik van systeemhulpmiddelen die in staat zijn om beheersmaatregelen voor systemen en toepassingen te omzeilen behoort te worden beperkt en nauwkeurig te worden gecontroleerd.	236
459	39	A.9.4.5	Access control to program source code	Access control to program source code	Toegangsbeveiliging op programmabroncode	Access to program source code should be restricted.	Access to program source code should be restricted.	Toegang tot de programmabroncode behoort te worden beperkt.	236
460	40	A.10.1.1	Policy on the use of cryptographic controls	Policy on the use of cryptographic controls	Beleid inzake het gebruik van cryptografische beheersmaatregelen	A policy on the use of cryptographic controls for protection of information should be developed and implemented.	A policy on the use of cryptographic controls for protection of information should be developed and implemented.	Ter bescherming van informatie behoort een beleid voor het gebruik van cryptografische beheersmaatregelen te worden ontwikkeld en gemplementeerd.	237
461	41	A.10.1.2	Key management	Key management	Sleutelbeheer	A policy on the use, protection and lifetime of cryptographic keys should be developed and implemented through their whole lifecycle.	A policy on the use, protection and lifetime of cryptographic keys should be developed and implemented through their whole lifecycle.	Met betrekking tot het gebruik, de bescherming en de levensduur van cryptografische sleutels behoort tijdens hun gehele levenscyclus een beleid te worden ontwikkeld en gemplementeerd.	237
462	42	A.11.1.1	Physical security perimeter	Physical security perimeter	Fysieke beveiligingszone	Security perimeters should be defined and used to protect areas that contain either sensitive or critical information and information processing facilities.	Security perimeters should be defined and used to protect areas that contain either sensitive or critical information and information processing facilities.	Beveiligingszones behoren te worden gedefinieerd en gebruikt om gebieden te beschermen die gevoelige of essentile informatie en informatieverwerkende faciliteiten bevatten.	238
463	43	A.11.1.2	Physical entry controls	Physical entry controls	Fysieke toegangsbeveiliging	Secure areas should be protected by appropriate entry controls to ensure that only authorized personnel are allowed access.	Secure areas should be protected by appropriate entry controls to ensure that only authorized personnel are allowed access.	Beveiligde gebieden behoren te worden beschermd door passende toegangsbeveiliging om ervoor te zorgen dat alleen bevoegd personeel toegang krijgt.	238
464	44	A.11.1.3	Securing offices, rooms and facilities	Securing offices, rooms and facilities	Kantoren, ruimten en faciliteiten beveiligen	Physical security for offices, rooms and facilities should be designed and applied.	Physical security for offices, rooms and facilities should be designed and applied.	Voor kantoren, ruimten en faciliteiten behoort fysieke beveiliging te worden ontworpen en toegepast.	238
465	45	A.11.1.4	Protecting against external and environmental threats	Protecting against external and environmental threats	Beschermen tegen bedreigingen van buitenaf	Physical protection against natural disasters, malicious attack or accidents should be designed and applied.	Physical protection against natural disasters, malicious attack or accidents should be designed and applied.	Tegen natuurrampen, kwaadwillige aanvallen of ongelukken behoort fysieke bescherming te worden ontworpen en toegepast.	238
466	46	A.11.1.5	Working in secure areas	Working in secure areas	Werken in beveiligde gebieden	Procedures for working in secure areas should be designed and applied.	Procedures for working in secure areas should be designed and applied.	Voor het werken in beveiligde gebieden behoren procedures te worden ontwikkeld en toegepast.	238
467	47	A.11.1.6	Delivery and loading areas	Delivery and loading areas	Laad- en loslocatie	Access points such as delivery and loading areas and other points where unauthorized persons could enter the premises should be controlled and, if possible, isolated from information processing facilities to avoid unauthorized access.	Access points such as delivery and loading areas and other points where unauthorized persons could enter the premises should be controlled and, if possible, isolated from information processing facilities to avoid unauthorized access.	Toegangspunten zoals laad- en loslocaties en andere punten waar onbevoegde personen het terrein kunnen betreden, behoren te worden beheerst, en zo mogelijk te worden afgeschermd van informatieverwerkende faciliteiten om onbevoegde toegang te vermijden.	238
468	48	A.11.2.1	Equipment siting and protection	Equipment siting and protection	Plaatsing en bescherming van apparatuur	Equipment should be sited and protected to reduce the risks from environmental threats and hazards, and opportunities for unauthorized access.	Equipment should be sited and protected to reduce the risks from environmental threats and hazards, and opportunities for unauthorized access.	Apparatuur behoort zo te worden geplaatst en beschermd dat risicos van bedreigingen en gevaren van buitenaf, alsook de kans op onbevoegde toegang worden verkleind.	239
469	49	A.11.2.2	Supporting utilities	Supporting utilities	Nutsvoorzieningen	Equipment should be protected from power failures and other disruptions caused by failures in supporting utilities.	Equipment should be protected from power failures and other disruptions caused by failures in supporting utilities.	Apparatuur behoort te worden beschermd tegen stroomuitval en andere verstoringen die worden veroorzaakt door ontregelingen in nutsvoorzieningen.	239
470	50	A.11.2.3	Cabling security	Cabling security	Beveiliging van bekabeling	Power and telecommunications cabling carrying data or supporting information services should be protected from interception, interference or damage.	Power and telecommunications cabling carrying data or supporting information services should be protected from interception, interference or damage.	Voedings- en telecommunicatiekabels voor het versturen van gegevens of die informatiediensten ondersteunen, behoren te worden beschermd tegen interceptie, verstoring of schade.	239
471	51	A.11.2.4	Equipment maintenance	Equipment maintenance	Onderhoud van apparatuur	Equipment should be correctly maintained to ensure its continued availability and integrity.	Equipment should be correctly maintained to ensure its continued availability and integrity.	Apparatuur behoort correct te worden onderhouden om de continue beschikbaarheid en integriteit ervan te waarborgen.	239
472	52	A.11.2.5	Removal of assets	Removal of assets	Verwijdering van bedrijfsmiddelen	Equipment, information or software should not be taken off-site without prior authorization.	Equipment, information or software should not be taken off-site without prior authorization.	Apparatuur, informatie en software behoren niet van de locatie te worden meegenomen zonder voorafgaande goedkeuring.	239
473	53	A.11.2.6	Security of equipment and assets off-premises	Security of equipment and assets off-premises	Beveiliging van apparatuur en bedrijfsmiddelen buiten het terrein	Security should be applied to off-site assets taking into account the different risks of working outside the organizations premises.	Security should be applied to off-site assets taking into account the different risks of working outside the organizations premises.	Bedrijfsmiddelen die zich buiten het terrein bevinden, behoren te worden beveiligd, waarbij rekening behoort te worden gehouden met de verschillende risicos van werken buiten het terrein van de organisatie.	239
474	54	A.11.2.7	Secure disposal or re-use of equipment	Secure disposal or re-use of equipment	Veilig verwijderen of hergebruiken van apparatuur	All items of equipment containing storage media should be verified to ensure that any sensitive data and licensed software has been removed or securely overwritten prior to disposal or re-use.	All items of equipment containing storage media should be verified to ensure that any sensitive data and licensed software has been removed or securely overwritten prior to disposal or re-use.	Alle onderdelen van de apparatuur die opslagmedia bevatten, behoren te worden geverifieerd om te waarborgen dat gevoelige gegevens en in licentie gegeven software voorafgaand aan verwijdering of hergebruik zijn verwijderd of betrouwbaar veilig zijn overschreven.	239
475	55	A.11.2.8	Unattended user equipment	Unattended user equipment	Onbeheerde gebruikersapparatuur	Users should ensure that unattended equipment has appropriate protection.	Users should ensure that unattended equipment has appropriate protection.	Gebruikers moeten ervoor zorgen dat onbeheerde apparatuur voldoende beschermd is.	239
476	56	A.11.2.9	Clear desk and clear screen policy	Clear desk and clear screen policy	Clear desk- en clear screen-beleid	A clear desk policy for papers and removable storage media and a clear screen policy for information processing facilities should be adopted.	A clear desk policy for papers and removable storage media and a clear screen policy for information processing facilities should be adopted.	Er behoort een clear desk-beleid voor papieren documenten en verwijderbare opslagmedia en een clear screen-beleid voor informatieverwerkende faciliteiten te worden ingesteld.	239
477	57	A.12.1.1	Documented operating procedures	Documented operating procedures	Gedocumenteerde bedieningsprocedures	Operating procedures should be documented and made available to all users who need them.	Operating procedures should be documented and made available to all users who need them.	Bedieningsprocedures behoren te worden gedocumenteerd en beschikbaar te worden gesteld aan alle gebruikers die ze nodig hebben.	240
478	58	A.12.1.2	Change management	Change management	Wijzigingsbeheer	Changes to the organization, business processes, information processing facilities and systems that affect information security should be controlled.	Changes to the organization, business processes, information processing facilities and systems that affect information security should be controlled.	Veranderingen in de organisatie, bedrijfsprocessen, informatieverwerkende faciliteiten en systemen die van invloed zijn op de informatiebeveiliging behoren te worden beheerst.	240
479	59	A.12.1.3	Capacity management	Capacity management	Capaciteitsbeheer	The use of resources should be monitored, tuned and projections made of future capacity requirements to ensure the required system performance.	The use of resources should be monitored, tuned and projections made of future capacity requirements to ensure the required system performance.	Het gebruik van middelen behoort te worden gemonitord en afgestemd, en er behoren verwachtingen te worden opgesteld voor toekomstige capaciteitseisen om de vereiste systeemprestaties te waarborgen.	240
480	60	A.12.1.4	Separation of development, testing and operational environments	Separation of development, testing and operational environments	Scheiding van ontwikkel-, test- en productieomgevingen	Development, testing, and operational environments should be separated to reduce the risks of unauthorized access or changes to the operational environment.	Development, testing, and operational environments should be separated to reduce the risks of unauthorized access or changes to the operational environment.	Ontwikkel-, test- en productieomgevingen behoren te worden gescheiden om het risico van onbevoegde toegang tot of veranderingen aan de productieomgeving te verlagen.	240
481	61	A.12.2.1	Controls against malware	Controls against malware	Beheersmaatregelen tegen malware	Detection, prevention and recovery controls to protect against malware should be implemented, combined with appropriate user awareness.	Detection, prevention and recovery controls to protect against malware should be implemented, combined with appropriate user awareness.	Ter bescherming tegen malware behoren beheersmaatregelen voor detectie, preventie en herstel te worden gemplementeerd, in combinatie met een passend bewustzijn van gebruikers.	241
482	62	A.12.3.1	Information backup	Information backup	Back-up van informatie	Backup copies of information, software and system images should be taken and tested regularly in accordance with an agreed backup policy.	Backup copies of information, software and system images should be taken and tested regularly in accordance with an agreed backup policy.	Regelmatig behoren back-upkopien van informatie, software en systeemafbeeldingen te worden gemaakt en getest in overeenstemming met een overeengekomen back-upbeleid.	242
483	63	A.12.4.1	Event logging	Event logging	Gebeurtenissen registreren	Event logs recording user activities, exceptions, faults and information security events should be produced, kept and regularly reviewed.	Event logs recording user activities, exceptions, faults and information security events should be produced, kept and regularly reviewed.	Logbestanden van gebeurtenissen die gebruikersactiviteiten, uitzonderingen en informatiebeveiligingsgebeurtenissen registreren, behoren te worden gemaakt, bewaard en regelmatig te worden beoordeeld.	243
484	64	A.12.4.2	Protection of log information	Protection of log information	Beschermen van informatie in logbestanden	Logging facilities and log information should be protected against tampering and unauthorized access.	Logging facilities and log information should be protected against tampering and unauthorized access.	Logfaciliteiten en informatie in logbestanden behoren te worden beschermd tegen vervalsing en onbevoegde toegang.	243
485	65	A.12.4.3	Administrator and operator logs	Administrator and operator logs	Logbestanden van beheerders en operators	System administrator and system operator activities should be logged and the logs protected and regularly reviewed.	System administrator and system operator activities should be logged and the logs protected and regularly reviewed.	Activiteiten van systeembeheerders en -operators behoren te worden vastgelegd en de logbestanden behoren te worden beschermd en regelmatig te worden beoordeeld.	243
486	66	A.12.4.4	Clock synchronisation	Clock synchronisation	Kloksynchronisatie	The clocks of all relevant information processing systems within an organization or security domain should be synchronised to a single reference time source.	The clocks of all relevant information processing systems within an organization or security domain should be synchronised to a single reference time source.	De klokken van alle relevante informatieverwerkende systemen binnen een organisatie of beveiligingsdomein behoren te worden gesynchroniseerd met n referentietijdbron.	243
487	67	A.12.5.1	Installation of software on operational systems	Installation of software on operational systems	Software installeren op operationele systemen	Procedures should be implemented to control the installation of software on operational systems.	Procedures should be implemented to control the installation of software on operational systems.	Om het op operationele systemen installeren van software te beheersen behoren procedures te worden gemplementeerd.	244
488	68	A.12.6.1	Management of technical vulnerabilities	Management of technical vulnerabilities	Beheer van technische kwetsbaarheden	Information about technical vulnerabilities of information systems being used should be obtained in a timely fashion, the organization's exposure to such vulnerabilities evaluated and appropriate measures taken to address the associated risk.	Information about technical vulnerabilities of information systems being used should be obtained in a timely fashion, the organization's exposure to such vulnerabilities evaluated and appropriate measures taken to address the associated risk.	Informatie over technische kwetsbaarheden van informatiesystemen die worden gebruikt behoort tijdig te worden verkregen, de blootstelling van de organisatie aan dergelijke kwetsbaarheden te worden gevalueerd en passende maatregelen te worden genomen om het risico dat ermee samenhangt aan te pakken.	245
489	69	A.12.6.2	Restrictions on software installation	Restrictions on software installation	Beperkingen voor het installeren van software	Rules governing the installation of software by users should be established and implemented.	Rules governing the installation of software by users should be established and implemented.	Voor het door gebruikers installeren van software behoren regels te worden vastgesteld en te worden gemplementeerd.	245
490	70	A.12.7.1	Information systems audit controls	Information systems audit controls	Beheersmaatregelen betreffende audits van informatiesystemen	Audit requirements and activities involving verification of operational systems should be carefully planned and agreed to minimize disruptions to business processes.	Audit requirements and activities involving verification of operational systems should be carefully planned and agreed to minimize disruptions to business processes.	Auditeisen en -activiteiten die verificatie van uitvoeringssystemen met zich meebrengen, behoren zorgvuldig te worden gepland en afgestemd om bedrijfsprocessen zo min mogelijk te verstoren.	246
491	71	A.13.1.1	Network controls	Network controls	Beheersmaatregelen voor netwerken	Networks should be managed and controlled to protect information in systems and applications.	Networks should be managed and controlled to protect information in systems and applications.	Netwerken behoren te worden beheerd en beheerst om informatie in systemen en toepassingen te beschermen.	247
492	72	A.13.1.2	Security of network services	Security of network services	Beveiliging van netwerkdiensten	Security mechanisms, service levels and management requirements of all network services should be identified and included in network services agreements, whether these services are provided in-house or outsourced.	Security mechanisms, service levels and management requirements of all network services should be identified and included in network services agreements, whether these services are provided in-house or outsourced.	Beveiligingsmechanismen, dienstverleningsniveaus en beheerseisen voor alle netwerkdiensten behoren te worden gedentificeerd en opgenomen in overeenkomsten betreffende netwerkdiensten. Dit geldt zowel voor diensten die intern worden geleverd als voor uitbestede diensten.	247
493	73	A.13.1.3	Segregation in networks	Segregation in networks	Scheiding in netwerken	Groups of information services, users and information systems should be segregated on networks.	Groups of information services, users and information systems should be segregated on networks.	Groepen van informatiediensten, -gebruikers en -systemen behoren in netwerken te worden gescheiden.	247
494	74	A.13.2.1	Information transfer policies and procedures	Information transfer policies and procedures	Beleid en procedures voor informatietransport	Formal transfer policies, procedures and controls should be in place to protect the transfer of information through the use of all types of communication facilities.	Formal transfer policies, procedures and controls should be in place to protect the transfer of information through the use of all types of communication facilities.	Ter bescherming van het informatietransport, dat via alle soorten communicatiefaciliteiten verloopt, behoren formele beleidsregels, procedures en beheersmaatregelen voor transport van kracht te zijn.	248
495	75	A.13.2.2	Agreements on information transfer	Agreements on information transfer	Overeenkomsten over informatietransport	Agreements should address the secure transfer of business information between the organization and external parties.	Agreements should address the secure transfer of business information between the organization and external parties.	Overeenkomsten behoren betrekking te hebben op het beveiligd transporteren van bedrijfsinformatie tussen de organisatie en externe partijen.	248
496	76	A.13.2.3	Electronic messaging	Electronic messaging	Elektronische berichten	Information involved in electronic messaging should be appropriately protected.	Information involved in electronic messaging should be appropriately protected.	Informatie die is opgenomen in elektronische berichten behoort passend te zijn beschermd.	248
497	77	A.13.2.4	Confidentiality or non-disclosure agreements	Confidentiality or non-disclosure agreements	Vertrouwelijkheids- of geheimhoudingsovereenkomst	Requirements for confidentiality or non-disclosure agreements reflecting the organizations needs for the protection of information should be identified, regularly reviewed and documented.	Requirements for confidentiality or non-disclosure agreements reflecting the organizations needs for the protection of information should be identified, regularly reviewed and documented.	Eisen voor vertrouwelijkheids- of geheimhoudingsovereenkomsten die de behoeften van de organisatie betreffende het beschermen van informatie weerspiegelen, behoren te worden vastgesteld, regelmatig te worden beoordeeld en gedocumenteerd.	248
498	78	A.14.1.1	Information security requirements analysis and specification	Information security requirements analysis and specification	Analyse en specificatie van informatiebeveiligingseisen	The information security related requirements should be included in the requirements for new information systems or enhancements to existing information systems.	The information security related requirements should be included in the requirements for new information systems or enhancements to existing information systems.	De eisen die verband houden met informatiebeveiliging behoren te worden opgenomen in de eisen voor nieuwe informatiesystemen of voor uitbreidingen van bestaande informatiesystemen.	249
499	79	A.14.1.2	Securing application services on public networks	Securing application services on public networks	Toepassingsdiensten op openbare netwerken beveiligen	Information involved in application services passing over public networks should be protected from fraudulent activity, contract dispute and unauthorized disclosure and modification.	Information involved in application services passing over public networks should be protected from fraudulent activity, contract dispute and unauthorized disclosure and modification.	Informatie die deel uitmaakt van uitvoeringsdiensten en die via openbare netwerken wordt uitgewisseld, behoort te worden beschermd tegen frauduleuze activiteiten, geschillen over contracten en onbevoegde openbaarmaking en wijziging.	249
500	80	A.14.1.3	Protecting application services transactions	Protecting application services transactions	Transacties van toepassingsdiensten beschermen	Information involved in application service transactions should be protected to prevent incomplete transmission, mis-routing, unauthorized message alteration, unauthorized disclosure, unauthorized message duplication or replay.	Information involved in application service transactions should be protected to prevent incomplete transmission, mis-routing, unauthorized message alteration, unauthorized disclosure, unauthorized message duplication or replay.	Informatie die deel uitmaakt van transacties van toepassingen behoort te worden beschermd ter voorkoming van onvolledige overdracht, foutieve routering, onbevoegd wijzigen van berichten, onbevoegd openbaar maken, onbevoegd vermenigvuldigen of afspelen.	249
501	81	A.14.2.1	Secure development policy	Secure development policy	Beleid voor beveiligd ontwikkelen	Rules for the development of software and systems should be established and applied to developments within the organization.	Rules for the development of software and systems should be established and applied to developments within the organization.	Voor het ontwikkelen van software en systemen behoren regels te worden vastgesteld en op ontwikkelactiviteiten binnen de organisatie te worden toegepast.	250
502	82	A.14.2.2	System change control procedures	System change control procedures	Procedures voor wijzigingsbeheer met betrekking tot systemen	Changes to systems within the development lifecycle should be controlled by the use of formal change control procedures.	Changes to systems within the development lifecycle should be controlled by the use of formal change control procedures.	Wijzigingen aan systemen binnen de levenscyclus van de ontwikkeling behoren te worden beheerst door het gebruik van formele procedures voor wijzigingsbeheer.	250
